unittitle_ssm: Evan A. Davis records on the U.S. House of Representatives Committee on the Judiciary Impeachment Inquiry
abstract_ssm: Pursuant to House Resolution 803 (H.Res.803 â€” 93rd Congress (1973-1974), an Impeachment Inquiry task force was formed to conduct an investigation as to whether sufficient grounds existed to impeach U.S. President Richard M. Nixon. This collection includes the copies of materials held by one of the inquiry staff members, counsel Evan Davis, that were compiled during the House Judiciary Committee's investigation. The bulk of the materials include the "statements of information" relevant to the investigation that were developed by the staff, with copies of the underlying supporting documentation
